<dl id="n09101c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09101c">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09101c"> 101(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> End of World</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the primitive church the influence of truth was very powerfully strengthened by an opinion which, however it may deserve respect for its usefulness and antiquity, has not been found agreeable to experience. It was universally believed that the end of the world, and the kingdom of heaven, were at hand. <small> Edward Gibbon, <a name="EGDF2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGDF2"><cite title="source">Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</cite></a> (ed. unknown) I, (Chapter XV) 452</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
